item.title: What to do when my compiler dont work?
item.dc:creator: @MaximusIV MaximusIV
item.description:
@MaximusIV wrote:

If your not sure if u have jdk installed go to your C drive then program files (x86) if you have 64 bit windows then java and there should be a folder that says jdk1.6.0_26 (yours may be different) what u need to do is edit your compiler to the version of jdk u have for example it well say

@echo off
“C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_26\bin\javac.exe” -classpath deps)

as u can see it has my jdk version there u just change urs to what ever version u have.

King Regards,
Aaran
